kind of work being important.

01:42:56.690 --> 01:42:58.430
And I think it's
important to think

01:42:58.430 --> 01:43:00.980
about how these things
change over time

01:43:00.980 --> 01:43:04.340
and how they don't necessarily
nicely and neatly line up

01:43:04.340 --> 01:43:07.350
with partisanship the way
that we imagine them to be,

01:43:07.350 --> 01:43:10.550
which brings me to my
question, which this plays out

01:43:10.550 --> 01:43:14.010
in particular ways when we
talk about intersectionality

01:43:14.010 --> 01:43:16.780
and when we talk not just
about women and conservatism

01:43:16.780 --> 01:43:19.690
but about African Americans
and conservatism, Latinos

01:43:19.690 --> 01:43:23.390
and conservatism, LGBTQ
and conservatism, Asians

01:43:23.390 --> 01:43:26.390
and conservatism,
and on and on and on.

01:43:26.390 --> 01:43:29.990
So I was just wondering, maybe,
if the panel could comment

01:43:29.990 --> 01:43:31.680
on some of the ways
that we can think

01:43:31.680 --> 01:43:34.500
about an archival
perspective of getting

01:43:34.500 --> 01:43:37.920
to those narratives that are
really, really hard to get to.

01:43:37.920 --> 01:43:39.510
And, particularly,
I'll just give you

01:43:39.510 --> 01:43:43.320
an example that I'm
familiar with, getting

01:43:43.320 --> 01:43:48.230
the papers of black women who
are conservative is really,

01:43:48.230 --> 01:43:49.490
really, really hard.

01:43:49.490 --> 01:43:52.740
Not because black women aren't
necessarily conservative,

01:43:52.740 --> 01:43:53.610
in fact they are.

01:43:53.610 --> 01:43:56.650
There are streams of
them and strains of them,

01:43:56.650 --> 01:43:58.830
but because that
conservatism rarely

01:43:58.830 --> 01:44:01.500
translates into partisanship.

01:44:01.500 --> 01:44:06.860
So the assumption is, or
the accurate assumption

01:44:06.860 --> 01:44:09.960
is, that black women are
the least likely to vote

01:44:09.960 --> 01:44:11.540
Republican.

01:44:11.540 --> 01:44:13.660
But actually, when we
look at conservatives,

01:44:13.660 --> 01:44:15.840
self-identified
conservatives, they

01:44:15.840 --> 01:44:18.640
are most likely
to be Black women.

01:44:18.640 --> 01:44:20.861
So how do you
solve that problem?

01:44:20.861 --> 01:44:21.360
Panel?

