01:45:00.300 --> 01:45:02.355
1981 to present day.

01:45:02.355 --> 01:45:03.230
- You're on your way.

01:45:05.950 --> 01:45:09.340
- Number one, let's
just underline the fact

01:45:09.340 --> 01:45:12.650
that you're pointing out an
important research methodology

01:45:12.650 --> 01:45:16.520
question for all of
conservatism, which

01:45:16.520 --> 01:45:18.660
those are not
synonymous categories,

01:45:18.660 --> 01:45:20.160
conservative and Republican.

01:45:20.160 --> 01:45:22.410
So, number one, we need to
get that category straight.

01:45:22.410 --> 01:45:25.700
And then number two, heartily
concur with what you're saying.

01:45:25.700 --> 01:45:28.450
And so I guess, as
conversations of this type

01:45:28.450 --> 01:45:30.480
are starting with
all conservatives,

01:45:30.480 --> 01:45:32.250
the diversity of
those conversations

01:45:32.250 --> 01:45:34.140
needs to be kept in mind.

01:45:34.140 --> 01:45:36.040
- Yeah.

01:45:36.040 --> 01:45:40.040
So I am thinking, first of
all, through personal papers

01:45:40.040 --> 01:45:41.700
of particular women.

01:45:41.700 --> 01:45:46.660
Also through nonpartisan
organizations of women

01:45:46.660 --> 01:45:49.670
who-- and you might
know of some--

01:45:49.670 --> 01:45:53.510
don't identify as Republican
but might identify

01:45:53.510 --> 01:45:56.270
in more conservative terms.

01:45:56.270 --> 01:45:58.640
And you better
