01:46:50.600 --> 01:46:53.410
by a number of
these people that we

01:46:53.410 --> 01:46:56.300
see doing this kind of work
that, again, doesn't translate

01:46:56.300 --> 01:46:57.750
into partisanship.

01:46:57.750 --> 01:47:00.330
I also think it's
worth looking within--

01:47:00.330 --> 01:47:06.040
and that's the grassroots part--
looking at a top-down approach.

01:47:06.040 --> 01:47:09.030
And so looking at how certain
policy initiatives are

01:47:09.030 --> 01:47:10.790
developed, political
initiatives,

01:47:10.790 --> 01:47:15.170
program initiatives that don't
necessarily look on their

01:47:15.170 --> 01:47:17.044
face a particular way.

01:47:17.044 --> 01:47:18.710
But when we look at
the nuts and bolts--

01:47:18.710 --> 01:47:24.240
and, again, maybe this is a plug
for the Kennedy School-- of how

01:47:24.240 --> 01:47:25.980
these things are
developed, it's not

01:47:25.980 --> 01:47:27.960
that it's republican-democrat,
but instead

01:47:27.960 --> 01:47:32.806
people who are coalescing
around very specific ideas.

01:47:32.806 --> 01:47:35.430
And I do think it's important as
